<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98717002262819></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98717002262819><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98717002262819>RE: Groups!?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98717002262819#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=887><span id=Sage>Zuranthium</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>390 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Apr 13th 9:53 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.95]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It sounds like you are doing good. The most important thing to remember is to not nuke too much on one monster. One or two nukes is enough per monster. Also, don't get into melee combat, it is a waste of your time. Always be meditating if you are not casting, directing your pet, or running away. Finally, be sure to use the right pet for the right situations. <br><br>Former Addict of Everquest.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
